    {
     "data": {
      "text/markdown": [
       "Notes:\n",
       "* The star is the location, after correction for a nearby blazar, of PKS J2333-2343. Because of that, it was not included.\n",
       "* There is a higher proportion of BL Lacs (11 %) than FSRQs (4 %)).\n",
       "* There are more steps-up (235) than steps-down (110), and the up-steps concentrate, with higher flux ratios, at the end,\n",
       "while the fewer down-steps are similarly concentrated at the start. These can be explained by the hypothesis that we are seeing transitions \n",
       "between discrete states, and the time spent in a higher state is less then the lower one. "
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "<utilities.ipynb_docgen.doc_formatter.<locals>.MimeBundleObject at 0x773c99cef760>"
      ]
